Rite Foods Limited, a manufacturer of carbonated soft drinks, sausages and energy drinks, has restated its commitment to corporate philanthropy with its sponsorship of actress, Eniola Badmus’ ‘Feeds the Needy’ initiative on New Year’s day in Lagos. The ‘Feeds the Needy’ initiative has been running since January 1, 2019, and the latest edition witnessed the feeding of over 50,000 underprivileged people, with Rite Foods providing an array of its refreshing beverages and snacks. The Assistant Brand Manager, Beverage and Bakery, Rite Foods Limited, Boluwatife Adedugbe, stated that the initiative was in line with the company’s commitment to corporate philanthropy. She said, “As a company, we are poised to strengthen global solidarity with a focus on meeting the needs of the poor and vulnerable people in different communities across the country.” On her part, Badmus commended the company for supporting the initiative. She said, “We have always been ensuring that smiles come to the faces of people in various communities across Lagos state and Nigeria in general. I appreciate the sponsors for helping me achieve the objective consecutively for four years.”  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com